# HTTPS CONNECT allowlist for the claude-oneshot --api-only sidecar.
# One host (or extended-regex pattern) per line. Comments start with `#`.
#
# Patterns are matched against the CONNECT destination host as extended
# regular expressions (FilterExtended On in tinyproxy.conf), so anchor
# with `^` and `$` when you want a literal match.
#
# Baseline reflects the hosts Claude Code typically needs for interactive
# startup, auth flows, and plugin marketplace metadata (per the published
# network configuration / install troubleshooting guides). Tighten it down
# (e.g. drop downloads.claude.ai once the image is built and auto-update
# is disabled) or widen it (e.g. add storage.googleapis.com for older
# native updater flows) to match your policy.

^api\.anthropic\.com$
^claude\.ai$
^platform\.claude\.com$
^downloads\.claude\.ai$
^raw\.githubusercontent\.com$
